<|r1|><**EU actions to combat climate change** ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s4|,|s5|,|s6|,|s7|,|s8|,|s9|><|supported|><|explain|><|r2|>< | Action area | Main measures / policies | Targets / outcomes | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s4|,|s5|,|s6|><|supported|><|explain|><|r3|><|------------|--------------------------|--------------------| ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s5|,|s6|><|supported|><|explain|><|r4|><| **Mitigation – emission cuts** | • European Climate Law (binding 55 % net GHG reduction by 2030, climate‑neutrality by 2050)
• Fit for 55 package (tightening EU ETS, CO₂ performance standards for cars, heavy‑duty vehicles, aviation, shipping)
• Carbon Border Adjustment Mechanism (CBAM) from 2026 to prevent carbon leakage
• Renewable energy push (24 % of final energy from renewables in 2023, historic high) | • Net‑55 % reduction vs 1990 by 2030
• Proposed 90 % net reduction by 2040 (interim target)
• >35 % drop in industrial GHG emissions (2005‑2023) | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s4|,|s5|,|s6|><|supported|><|explain|><|r5|><| **Decarbonising industry & energy** | • Large‑scale electrification, hydrogen rollout, renewable material substitution
• Phase‑out of fossil‑fuel subsidies
• Support for clean‑technology innovation (≈27 % of global cleantech patents 2017‑2021) | • 24 % renewable share in final energy (2023)
• Fossil fuels still ~70 % of gross energy use – further investment needed | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s5|,|s6|><|supported|><|explain|><|r6|><| **Adaptation & resilience** | • EU Adaptation Strategy (2021) – smarter, faster, systemic adaptation
• EU Preparedness Union Strategy – integrated climate‑risk management
• Funding via EU Solidarity Fund, NextGenerationEU, Civil Protection Mechanism | • All Member States have national adaptation policies; many have sectoral plans
• Goal to protect people, prosperity and critical infrastructure from climate extremes | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s7|,|s8|><|supported|><|explain|><|r7|><| **Nature‑based solutions & biodiversity** | • Nature Restoration Regulation (aim to restore ≥20 % of land & sea by 2030)
• Circular‑economy actions (Zero‑Pollution Action Plan, micro‑plastic restrictions) | • Protected‑area extent increased over the past decade
• Ongoing effort to reverse biodiversity loss and improve ecosystem health | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s8|><|supported|><|explain|><|r8|><| **Governance & finance** | • EU ETS (including new ETS 2 for road transport)
• Governance Regulation (Article 17/19) – reporting on climate justice (see map of country mentions)
• Public & private financing mechanisms to scale mitigation & adaptation | • 62 % of 154 EGD targets on track (mid‑2024)
• 30 % of EU budget earmarked for climate‑related spending (2021‑2027) | ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s8|><|supported|><|explain|><|r9|>< *Key sources:* EU climate‑law targets, Fit for 55, CBAM, renewable‑energy share, adaptation strategy, nature‑restoration regulation, and funding programmes are described in the European environment report 2025 [[1]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/main-report/report/@@download/file). ><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s1|><|supported|><|explain|><|r10|><|subclaims|><|cite|><|s9|><|supported|><|explain|>
